How to build primesieve:

  1. Microsoft Visual C++
    Open a Visual Studio Command Prompt, cd into the primesieve
    directory and run:
    > nmake -f Makefile.msvc
  
  2. GNU G++ Compiler 
    Open a terminal, cd into the primesieve directory and run:
    $ make
    
  3. Other C++ Compilers
    Open a terminal, cd into the primesieve directory and run:
    $ make CXX=my_compiler

How to test primesieve:

  1. Windows
    > out\primesieve.exe 1 1000 -p1
    Prints the prime numbers up to 1000 to the standard output.
    
  2. Unix-like operating systems (Linux, Mac OS X, Solaris, ...)
    $ out/./primesieve 1 1e10 -s 32 -c1 -c2
    Sets the sieve size to 32 KiloBytes and counts the prime numbers
    and twin primes between 1 and 10^10.
